Edition:
Quote:  The old Maori-myth names of the islands Eaheinomawe and Tavai Poinammoo, as Cook calls them, or Ika-na-mawe and Tavai-Pounamu as D'Urville more correctly calls them, still disfigure many maps, but are utterly obsolete for all practical purposes.
